  "data_kind": "probabilities",
  "coverage": "Complete coverage of both tournaments: all 64 matches of the 2018 FIFA World Cup (Russia) and all 64 matches of the 2022 FIFA World Cup (Qatar), 128 matches total. Each match has FiveThirtyEight's SPI-based pre-match win/draw/loss probabilities (prob1=p_home, probtie=p_draw, prob2=p_away). team1 is treated as home and team2 as away. Probabilities sum to ~1.0 on every row. NOTE: all knockout-stage matches have p_draw=0.0 — this is FiveThirtyEight's published convention (they fold extra-time/penalty outcomes into the two win probabilities for elimination games), not missing data. One team-name normalization applied: 'USA' -> 'United States'; all other names were already standard English. Source CSVs are no longer live (FiveThirtyEight/projects.fivethirtyeight.com was shut down in 2025 and now redirects to ABC News HTML); data was pulled from Wayback Machine archived snapshots of the original projects.fivethirtyeight.com/soccer-api CSVs. 2022 from the post-tournament 2023-06-01 snapshot, 2018 from the 2019-10-07 snapshot — both contain the full completed bracket.",
  "sources": [
   "https://web.archive.org/web/20191007083746id_/https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/soccer-api/international/2018/wc_matches.csv",
   "https://web.archive.org/web/20230601154834id_/https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/soccer-api/international/2022/wc_matches.csv",
   "https://github.com/fivethirtyeight/data/tree/master/world-cup-2018",
   "https://github.com/fivethirtyeight/data/tree/master/world-cup-2022"
  ],
